	<Notes>
		^x7070FF^xD02090^xC8C8C8^7rough plan on gem priority, may need adjustment depending on how run goes
normally prefer to upgrade single target first over clear, except first lvl3 gem has to be ed
^xD02090
SKILLS^7

lvl1:
volcano
contagion
frost bomb
entangle (consider doing mud burrow, its technically a waste of time but makes run much nicer and more reliable)

lvl3:
essence drain
frost darts (if no weapon) / volcano if prefered
pounce
wing blast

lvl5:
Bone Storm
Thunder Storm

lvl7:
leap slam (might not be needed since we have to finish run at 36 anyway)

^xD02090SUPPORTS^7

t1 support:
unleash (swap single/clear, its nice for entangle)
zenith
chain (ed)
magnified effect
swift afflication (ed)
rapid casting (bonestorm)
duration (pounce)

t2 support
living lightning (thunderstorm)
momentum (bonestorm)
considered casting (bonestorm)
mark on death (pounce)
intense agonyt x2 (ed, contagion)

t3 support
zenith 2

^xD02090SPIRIT^7
I dont know they all seem bad, arctic armour and time of need or something

^xD02090BOSSING^7
run start: maintain exposure from frost bomb -&gt; fully channel volcano (ideally against wall if possible)

pre bonestorm: frost bomb and ideally we get a lvl2/3 staff (lightning bolt/fireball, chaos bolt is not bad as well if combined with ed), otherwise volcano/frost darts depending on preference

bonestorm:
pre cast bonestorm before fight (to get impale stacks)
maintain pounce mark for armour break
maintain thunderstorm for shock and living lightning
when possible wing blast -&gt; pounce -&gt; rend (cancel animation) (this is not that good, if you struggle with animation cancelling you can skip this bit)
spam bonestorm, make sure to cover enough distance for momentum before releasing, for bosses with large hit boxes its often worth to fully channel it
	</Notes>
